title: 568386N
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted from fresh tissue samples by TRIzol Reagent (Invitrogen life technologies) according to the recommended protocols.
label_protocol_ch1: mRNAs were labeled with the Quick Amp Labeling Kit, One-Color (Agilent p/n 5190-0442), according to the manufacturer’s guidelines.
hyb_protocol: After stopping the labeling procedure, Agilent Gene Expression Hybridization Kit (Agilent p/n 5188-5242) was used for mRNAs hybridization according to the manufacturer’s instructions. Hybridize at 65°C for 17 hours.
scan_protocol: The hybridized chips were scanned with an Agilent Microarray Scanner (Agilent p/n G2565BA).
description: Agilent Whole Genome Oligo Microarrays (one-color): Prepare the RNA Sample; Total RNA Clean-up and RNA QC; Prepare labeling reaction; Purify the labeled/amplified RNA and labeled cRNA QC; Hybridization; Microarray Wash; Scanning; Extract data using Agilent Feature Extraction Software;
data_processing: Agilent Feature Extraction Software is used to read the raw intensity of the image. Add the images (.tif) to be extracted to the FE Project; Set FE Project Properties; Check the Extraction Set Configuration; Save the FE Project (.fep) by selecting File > Save As and browse for desired location; Select Project > Start Extracting and export data to txt.
data_processing.1: Normalized intensity was regarded as mRNA expression level according to the recommended calculation methods.
contact_institute: The First Affiliated Hospital, Sun Yat-sen University
